      • toArray

        public E[] toArray​(E[] elems)
        Returns an array containing all of the elements in this list in proper sequence (from first to last element). As you know, we cannot create arrays of generic types. Here we circumvent the problem by asking the caller to create the array for us. The caller knows both the runtime type and the number of elements. See Pastiche.allPairs for an example.
        Parameters:
        elems - the reference of array where the elements will be stored.
        Returns:
        the reference of the array
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the size of the array is not exactly the same as the size of this list
